        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName><hi rend="print">Down. | Bromley. | Kent. S.E.</hi></placeName>
                    <date>July 12<hi rend="superscript">th</hi>.</date>
                    <salute>My dear Bentham</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>I write merely to thank you very sincerely for the specimens which I have long wished to examine &amp; for your information wh. will be very useful to me.<ref target="#foot.f2"/></p>
<p>Believe me | yours very sincerely | Ch. Darwin</p> 
                </div>
            </div>
            
        </div>

        

        

        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">The year is established by the reference to the specimens sent with the <ref target="./DCP-LETT-4556.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter from George Bentham, 10 July 1864</ref>.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f2">See <ref target="./DCP-LETT-4556.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter from George Bentham, 10 July 1864</ref> and n. 1.</note>
        </div>        
            
